Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g}, ~{8-10%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, open the remaining sachets.

Add the @Zanzibar Style Curry Powder{1%sachet}, @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Creme Fraiche{75%g} and @Water for the Curry{100%ml} to the chicken.

Stir and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @Peas{120%g} and half the @Mango Chutney{40%g}. Simmer, ~{1%minute}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share your rice and curry between #bowls{}.

Drizzle over the remaining mango chutney to finish.

Enjoy!